From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:09:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] xargs: wire spawned children's stdio to the box's logical
 streams
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The commands xargs spawns inherited the engine's real fd 1/2, so a
child's stdout/stderr ignored the box's pipes and redirects — `xargs cmd
| next` and `xargs cmd > file` (the everyday xargs patterns) silently
misrouted to the terminal. That made in-process xargs only half-correct.

Fix: add `child_stdout`/`child_stderr` to the `XargsIo` seam (default
`None` = inherit, so the standalone binary is byte-identical), set them on
the child `Command` before spawn, and have the in-process builtin dup the
shell's logical stdout/stderr `OpenFile`s into them via the existing
`TryFrom<OpenFile> for Stdio` (a piped/redirected sink is dup'd, an
inherited handle stays inherit, an fd-less in-memory stream becomes null).
The builtin now captures fd 1/2 as `OpenFile`s (try_fd) and uses them both
as xargs's own output sink and as the child-stdio source.

Verified on the static musl build: `seq 3 | xargs echo | wc -w` -> 3 (was
0), `printf hello | xargs echo > file` -> file holds "hello" (was empty),
child `2>` honored; plain xargs and logical cwd unaffected; xargs unit
suite 10/10.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B5MwFcipu6iwqtMPPwFhXd
---
 src/xargs/mod.rs | 23 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/xargs/mod.rs b/src/xargs/mod.rs
index 58d2e33..edf2e71 100644
--- a/src/xargs/mod.rs
+++ b/src/xargs/mod.rs
@@ -39,6 +39,16 @@ pub trait XargsIo {
     fn output(&self) -> &RefCell<dyn Write>;
     /// Sink for diagnostics (`-t` command traces, warnings, errors).
     fn error_output(&self) -> &RefCell<dyn Write>;
+    /// Stdio for a spawned child's stdout / stderr. An embedder returns
+    /// `Some(_)` to route the child's output to the shell's logical streams
+    /// (e.g. a dup of a piped/redirected logical fd); the default `None` leaves
+    /// the child inheriting the process fds, matching the standalone binary.
+    fn child_stdout(&self) -> Option<Stdio> {
+        None
+    }
+    fn child_stderr(&self) -> Option<Stdio> {
+        None
+    }
 }
 
 /// The dependencies used when xargs runs as the real standalone executable:
@@ -513,6 +523,19 @@ impl CommandBuilder<'_> {
             let _ = err.flush();
         }
 
+        // Route the spawned child's stdout/stderr to the embedder's logical
+        // streams when provided. The in-process builtin dups the shell's
+        // logical fds here, so `xargs cmd > file` / `xargs cmd | next` honor
+        // the box's redirects and pipes. Default (standalone) leaves the child
+        // inheriting the process fds, exactly as upstream does. Set after the
+        // `-t` trace so the verbose output is unchanged.
+        if let Some(s) = io.child_stdout() {
+            command.stdout(s);
+        }
+        if let Some(s) = io.child_stderr() {
+            command.stderr(s);
+        }
+
         match &self.options.action {
             ExecAction::Command(_) => match command.status() {
                 Ok(status) => {
